MZANSI has recorded 1160 new positive coronavirus cases on
Sunday. This is the biggest number the Mzansi has ever seen in one day.  Now the total number of positive coronavirus cases stands
at 15 515. Minister of Health Zweli Mkhize said that of the new 1160
cases, 890 are from the Western Cape. The total number of recoveries so far is 7 006. A total of 460 873 tests have been conducted. "Regrettably, we report a further 3 Covid-19 related
deaths and this brings the total number of deaths to 264. "We wish to express our condolences to the loved
ones of the departed and thank the healthcare workers who cared for the
deceased," said Mkhize. 